article.description: Emanuel Miller scored 20 points and Texas A&M erased a double-digit deficit in the second half and beat Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 63-60 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Texas A&M rallies to beat Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 63-60
article.linkText: Texas A&M rallies to beat Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 63-60
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- — Rasheed Browne had 20 points as Texas A&M-Corpus Christi got past Texas A&M-International 64-53 on Wednesday night. Jalen White had 14 points and 14 rebounds for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi (1-0). Perry Francois added 12 points and seven rebounds. Jamyus Jones had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Dustdevils. Darrell Jones added 13 points. Daniel Kiely had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
